I work with small businesses. If you need a new website or your current website isn't working, I can help. I'll also get you up and running on Facebook and Twitter.
		
Email me at **leon . paternoster @ unseen . is** (without spaces) for more information.

## <a href="http://suffolklibraries.co.uk">Suffolk Libraries</a>
	
I redesigned and built the Suffolk Libraries website in 2014. The project involved:

- Research into customer requirements (using a <a href="http://www.customercarewords.com/what-it-is.html">&#8216;top task&#8217; methodology</a>)
- Stakeholder interviews
- Research into the site structure (using <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Card_sorting">customer card sort</a> exercises)
- Testing
- Building a <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Child_Themes">WordPress child theme</a>

## <a href="http://cultcafe.co.uk">Cult cafe</a>
	
Responsive site for the popular cafe and live music venue on Ipswich waterfront. The project involved:

- Research into music venue and cafe website top tasks, especially for a student audience
- Designing the look of the site
- Arranging hosting
- Building a WordPress theme
- Incorporating Google Calendar events

## <a href="http://allsortzgroup.co.uk">Allsortz Theatre Group</a>
	
A simple one page site. This project involved:

- Researching the client's work
- Using <a href="https://pages.github.com/">Github Pages</a> to set up simple, free and fast hosting
- Designing the look of the site
- Embedding a Vimeo film that scales when visitors visit the site with a mobile phone

All my work is responsive, which means your site will work and look good on any phone, tablet, laptop or PC.

